Children as young as seven can take part in bull riding competitions . 
 Youngest children ride calves before graduating to bullocks then bulls . 
 Between four and six, they hone their skills by 'mutton busting' on sheep . 
 Bull riding is thought to be one of the most dangerous sports in the world . 
 An estimated one in every 15 bull rides ends in some sort of injury . 
